text:
Good:
- active noise cancelling does its job;
- when on battery sound quality is good;
- when wearing glasses, passive insulation is ok with it (not perfect, of course, and not for thick temples);
- overall comfortable, though active noise cancelling could become uncomfortable for ear after some time of continuous wearing;
- could be somewhat flattened and fit backpack, have case as well;


Not good:
- terrible sound when on AUX cable without post-processing, meaning could not be really used without charged battery;
- if connected via cable cannot enable the said post-processing, need to disconnect first, then power on;
- Bluetooth does not connect when headphones are plugged via cable, makes it difficult to use phone app;
- it is not possible to really disable touch buttons, they still continue to produce sound when touched;
- surface is fingerprints magnet, not that obvious but still not eye pleasing (I have black coloured version);
- AUX cable is a bit lacking, also - very subjectively and to me personally - angled cable is inconvenient.

